---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About">

  <!-- HERO, slightly darker to distinguish from body -->
  <section class="relative bg-gray-950 border-b border-gray-800 overflow-hidden">
    <img
      src="/images/blueprint-hero-bg.png"
      alt=""
      class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover opacity-40"
    />
    <div class="relative max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-28 text-center">
      <p class="text-blue-400 text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-8">
        Jon Eric Soderberg, Ph.D.
      </p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold leading-[1.15] tracking-tight mb-8 text-white">
        The right data, in the right place, at the right time, without human error in the chain.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed mb-10 max-w-xl mx-auto">
        Business Analytics &amp; Data Science &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; Senior Federal Leader &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; 35-Year Fire Service &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; Educator
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/cv" class="bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg transition-colors text-sm">
          Curriculum Vitae
        </a>
        <a href="/publications" class="border border-gray-600 hover:border-gray-400 hover:bg-gray-800 text-gray-300 hover:text-white font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg transition-colors text-sm">
          Research
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ABOUT -->
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-16 pb-4">
    <p class="text-gray-300 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-5">
      My work sits at the intersection of data science, geospatial technology, federal policy, and operational
      leadership. I hold a Ph.D. in Business Analytics and Data Science (Capital Technology University, 2026)
      and an M.S. in Geographical Information Systems (Penn State, 2011).
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-300 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-3">
      The fascination with maps predates the degrees, and it probably started on the floor with a
      National Geographic supplement unfolded across the carpet, more poster than reference, built
      to put a continent or an ocean floor in front of a kid who had never seen either. From there
      it became Sanborn fire insurance maps, topographic quadrangles, General Land Office plats, old
      railroad survey maps, all of it.
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-300 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      Each one is a record of what a surveyor decided mattered enough to walk the ground and measure
      by hand. A Sanborn map encodes building material, roofline, and water source because fire risk
      depended on it. A topo sheet encodes elevation because a triangulation crew climbed the high
      points and ran the angles themselves. A General Land Office plat encodes section corners because
      a chain man set a stone or marked a witness tree, and that mark became the legal basis for who
      owned what. Lewis and Clark charted a continent with a compass, a chronometer that drifted, dead
      reckoning corrected by the stars, and information from people who already knew the ground far
      better than any instrument could. Harold Fisk's Mississippi River meander maps did something
      different again: not surveying the present, but reconstructing centuries of the river's abandoned
      channels from oxbow scars and sediment terraces, reading the residue a moving system leaves
      behind to rebuild a timeline nobody directly observed. Every one of these maps is a snapshot of
      how much truth someone could extract from the world given the tools, the time, and the evidence
      available to them. That is the same question data science asks today, just answered faster and
      at a different scale. The questions never changed. Only the cost of answering them did.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- IDENTITY CARDS -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-5">

      <a href="/publications" class="group border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-8 hover:border-gray-600 hover:bg-gray-750 transition-all duration-200 hover:-translate-y-0.5 block">
        <svg class="w-5 h-5 mb-5 text-gray-500 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9.75 3.104v5.714a2.25 2.25 0 0 1-.659 1.591L5 14.5M9.75 3.104c-.251.023-.501.05-.75.082m.75-.082a24.301 24.301 0 0 1 4.5 0m0 0v5.714c0 .597.237 1.17.659 1.591L19.8 15.3M14.25 3.104c.251.023.501.05.75.082M19.8 15.3l-1.57.393A9.065 9.065 0 0 1 12 15a9.065 9.065 0 0 0-6.23-.693L5 14.5m14.8.8 1.402 1.402c1.232 1.232.65 3.318-1.067 3.611A48.309 48.309 0 0 1 12 21c-2.773 0-5.491-.235-8.135-.687-1.718-.293-2.3-2.379-1.067-3.61L5 14.5" /></svg>
        <h2 class="text-base font-bold mb-2 text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Research</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Ph.D. research in data quality and automated legislative document processing.
          USLM Parser: 4.8M–9.6M&times; efficiency gain over manual transcription. 0.0% cross-format inconsistency.
        </p>
        <span class="text-blue-400 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide">Publications &amp; software →</span>
      </a>

      <a href="/cv" class="group border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-8 hover:border-gray-600 transition-all duration-200 hover:-translate-y-0.5 block">
        <svg class="w-5 h-5 mb-5 text-gray-500 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 21v-8.25M15.75 21v-8.25M8.25 21v-8.25M3 9l9-6 9 6m-1.5 12V10.332A48.36 48.36 0 0 0 12 9.75c-2.551 0-5.056.2-7.5.582V21M3 21h18M12 6.75h.008v.008H12V6.75Z" /></svg>
        <h2 class="text-base font-bold mb-2 text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Federal Career</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
          25+ years in federal civil service. Currently leading the largest information system transformation
          in the organization's history, overseeing 25,000+ active projects globally.
        </p>
        <span class="text-blue-400 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide">Experience &amp; CV →</span>
      </a>

      <a href="/cv#fire" class="group border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-8 hover:border-gray-600 transition-all duration-200 hover:-translate-y-0.5 block">
        <svg class="w-5 h-5 mb-5 text-gray-500 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M15.362 5.214A8.252 8.252 0 0 1 12 21 8.25 8.25 0 0 1 6.038 7.047 8.287 8.287 0 0 0 9 9.601a8.983 8.983 0 0 1 3.361-6.867 8.21 8.21 0 0 0 3 2.48Z" /><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 18a3.75 3.75 0 0 0 .495-7.468 5.99 5.99 0 0 0-1.925 3.547 5.975 5.975 0 0 1-2.133-1.001A3.75 3.75 0 0 0 12 18Z" /></svg>
        <h2 class="text-base font-bold mb-2 text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Fire Service</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
          35+ years of operational service as firefighter, fire officer, hazmat technician, and emergency
          services instructor. Certified at the national level; currently on a Board of Directors.
        </p>
        <span class="text-blue-400 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide">Certifications &amp; service →</span>
      </a>

      <a href="/teaching" class="group border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-8 hover:border-gray-600 transition-all duration-200 hover:-translate-y-0.5 block">
        <svg class="w-5 h-5 mb-5 text-gray-500 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M4.26 10.147a60.438 60.438 0 0 0-.491 6.347A48.62 48.62 0 0 1 12 20.904a48.62 48.62 0 0 1 8.232-4.41 60.46 60.46 0 0 0-.491-6.347m-15.482 0a50.636 50.636 0 0 0-2.658-.813A59.906 59.906 0 0 1 12 3.493a59.903 59.903 0 0 1 10.399 5.84c-.896.248-1.783.52-2.658.814m-15.482 0A50.717 50.717 0 0 1 12 13.489a50.702 50.702 0 0 1 3.741-3.342M6.75 15a.75.75 0 1 0 0-1.5.75.75 0 0 0 0 1.5Zm0 0v-3.675A55.378 55.378 0 0 1 12 8.443m-7.007 11.55A5.981 5.981 0 0 0 6.75 15.75v-1.5" /></svg>
        <h2 class="text-base font-bold mb-2 text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Teaching</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
          National instructor at a Federal Learning Center (IACET Authorized Provider). Building toward
          a second career in university education in data science and GIS.
        </p>
        <span class="text-blue-400 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide">Courses &amp; portfolio →</span>
      </a>

      <a href="/pai" class="group border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-8 hover:border-gray-600 transition-all duration-200 hover:-translate-y-0.5 block md:col-span-2">
        <svg class="w-5 h-5 mb-5 text-gray-500 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9.813 15.904 9 18.75l-.813-2.846a4.5 4.5 0 0 0-3.09-3.09L2.25 12l2.846-.813a4.5 4.5 0 0 0 3.09-3.09L9 5.25l.813 2.846a4.5 4.5 0 0 0 3.09 3.09L15.75 12l-2.846.813a4.5 4.5 0 0 0-3.09 3.09ZM18.259 8.715 18 9.75l-.259-1.035a3.375 3.375 0 0 0-2.455-2.456L14.25 6l1.036-.259a3.375 3.375 0 0 0 2.455-2.456L18 2.25l.259 1.035a3.375 3.375 0 0 0 2.456 2.456L21.75 6l-1.035.259a3.375 3.375 0 0 0-2.456 2.456ZM16.894 20.567 16.5 21.75l-.394-1.183a2.25 2.25 0 0 0-1.423-1.423L13.5 18.75l1.183-.394a2.25 2.25 0 0 0 1.423-1.423l.394-1.183.394 1.183a2.25 2.25 0 0 0 1.423 1.423l1.183.394-1.183.394a2.25 2.25 0 0 0-1.423 1.423Z" /></svg>
        <h2 class="text-base font-bold mb-2 text-white group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Yggdrasil, Personal AI Infrastructure</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
          A Life Operating System built on Norse mythology. Odin orchestrates 16 specialist components, Frigg plans, Heimdall watches, Mimir stores wisdom, Huginn collects, Muninn remembers, Thor protects, Loki breaks things on purpose. The World Tree, running as software.
        </p>
        <span class="text-blue-400 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide">System architecture &amp; the Norse hierarchy →</span>
      </a>

    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
